The Group Managing Director SystemSpecs John Obaro has identified vision and exemplary leadership as some of the qualities to succeed as an entrepreneur in the marketplace in Africa. The technology expert spoke at the maiden edition of Switch, an interdenominational youth summit, aimed at mentoring younger and upcoming ministers, organised by the Foursquare Gospel Church at the church’s headquarters in Yaba, Lagos. Other speakers include the General Overseer, Foursquare Gospel Church, Revd Sam Aboyeji; the Secretary-General, Bible Society of Nigeria (BSN), Pastor Samuel Sanusi;  founder, Mount Zion Faith Ministries International, Mike Bamiloye; and his wife, Gloria. Speaking on the topic, ‘30 Levers to Fly in the Marketplace’, the technology icon highlighted 30 qualities needed by Christians to succeed in business.   Global Fund, others to tackle malaria with $18b     Unity Bank empowers women entrepreneurs with Yanga     MAN lauds Henkel for its commitment to economy   Helisted the five Cs of exemplary leadership, which include critical thinking, creativity, confidence, collaboration and character. Obaro emphasised the power of vision in actualising dreams. “If your vision does not provide a solution to a problem, it is just a mere ambition,” he said. Obaro, also a member of the National Convention of the Foursquare Gospel Church,  highlighted the benefits of prayers in making business decisions. “I have no power, but I run to the one who has all the power,” the technology chief said. Obaro, a former banker, founded SystemSpecs in 1992. The company has grown over the years into a renowned provider of financial, human capital management and ecommerce technology solutions, with popular products like Remita, HumanManager, and Paylink. This year, SystemSpecs celebrates 30 years since inception, marking three decades of innovation and impact.